Based on my research, I can provide you with a clear picture of how Meta's WhatsApp Terms of Service relate to projects like SUBZERO-MD.
What SUBZERO-MD Is
SUBZERO-MD is a WhatsApp Multi-Device Bot built using unofficial reverse-engineered libraries (like Baileys/angularsockets) that interact with WhatsApp Web's WebSocket protocol directly, bypassing the official WhatsApp Business API.
Meta's Terms of Service Position
WhatsApp's Terms of Service explicitly prohibit this type of usage. You must not directly, indirectly, through automated or other means: (a) reverse engineer, alter, modify, create derivative works from, decompile, or extract code from our Services WhatsApp
The WhatsApp Business Terms add further restrictions: Company must not directly, indirectly, or through automated or other means: (e) reverse engineer any aspect of our Business Services or do anything that may discover source code; (g) develop or use any applications that interact with our Business Services without our prior written consent. WhatsApp

Key Risks

Account bans - WhatsApp actively detects and bans accounts using unofficial clients
No official support - Changes to WhatsApp's protocol can break functionality at any time
Security concerns - Using unofficial libraries can expose you to malicious forks (recently documented cases of data-stealing packages masquerading as legitimate Baileys forks)
Terms violation - Clear breach of WhatsApp's ToS, which could have legal implications depending on jurisdiction and use case
